You shouldn&#39;t use an array as the key of a `HashMap`, since arrays don&#39;t override `equals` and `hashCode`, so different array instances that contain the exact same elements are not considered identical by the `HashMap`.

Use `List&lt;Integer&gt;` keys instead.

    Map&lt;List&lt;Integer&gt;, Integer&gt; hm = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
    
    List&lt;Integer&gt; a = List.of(1, 1, 0, 0);
    List&lt;Integer&gt; b = List.of(1, 1, 0, 0);
    
    hm.put(a,1);
    
    if (!hm.containsKey(b)) {
        //key does not exists so, create new one  
        hm.put(b, 1);
    }
    else {
        //key does exists so, put its value = value + 1
        hm.put(b, hm.get(b)+1); 
    }

